This paper deals with change detection in remote sensing images using machine learning techniques. The paper proposes a framework based on image regression, which involves learning a transformation to map one image to the domain of another image. This is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses various regression methods such as Gaussian processes, support vector machines, random forests, and kernel regression, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves optimization of hyperparameters, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves data analysis and experimentation, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data science (cs.DS).
